        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 29 at 6:19PM EDT until April 29 at 7:00PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>SVRBGM

The National Weather Service in Binghamton has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
West central Steuben County in central New York...

* Until 700 PM EDT.

* At 618 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Hartsville,
or 8 miles south of Hornell, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Hartsville, Savona, Bath, Cameron, Cameron Mills, Risingville,
Canisteo, North Cameron, West Cameron, and West Greenwood.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
